Problem 1

Determine the number of solutions that the system has in relation to parameters aaa and bbb:

{ax+7z=2,−2x−y=1,−4x−6y+bz=−4\begin{cases}ax+7z=2, \\-2x-y=1,\\-4x-6y+bz=-4\end{cases}⎩⎨⎧​ax+7z=2,−2x−y=1,−4x−6y+bz=−4​

Rewrite as a matrix:

(a07∣2−2−10∣1−4−6b∣−4)∼(a07∣2210∣−180b∣−6)\begin{pmatrix}a & 0 & 7 & \bigm| & 2\\-2 & -1 & 0 & \bigm| & 1 \\ -4 & -6 & b & \bigm| &-4 \end{pmatrix}\sim\begin{pmatrix}a & 0 & 7 & \bigm| & 2\\2 & 1 & 0 & \bigm| & -1 \\ 8 & 0 & b & \bigm| &-6 \end{pmatrix}​a−2−4​0−1−6​70b​​​​​21−4​​∼​a28​010​70b​​​​​2−1−6​​

2nd does not depend on a,ba, ba,b, so consider the following matrix:

(a07∣280b∣−6)∼(a07∣2830b3∣−2)∼(a+8307+b3∣0830b3∣−2)\begin{pmatrix}a & 0 & 7 & \bigm| & 2\\ 8 & 0 & b & \bigm| &-6 \end{pmatrix}\sim\begin{pmatrix}a & 0 & 7 & \bigm| & 2\\ \frac{8}{3} & 0 & \frac{b}{3} & \bigm| &-2 \end{pmatrix}\sim\begin{pmatrix}a+\frac{8}{3} & 0 & 7+\frac{b}{3} & \bigm| & 0\\ \frac{8}{3} & 0 & \frac{b}{3} & \bigm| &-2 \end{pmatrix}(a8​00​7b​​​​2−6​)∼(a38​​00​73b​​​​​2−2​)∼(a+38​38​​00​7+3b​3b​​​​​0−2​)

For the number of solutions to be infinite, we need a line that would have all zeros. Therefore, the system above has infinite solutions if:

{a+83=07+b3=0⇒{a=−83b=−21\begin{cases}a+\frac{8}{3}=0\\7+\frac{b}{3}=0\end{cases}\Rightarrow\begin{cases}a=-\frac{8}{3}\\b=-21\end{cases}{a+38​=07+3b​=0​⇒{a=−38​b=−21​

For the number of solutions to be zero, we need a line that would have all zeros except for the number coefficent. Consider all cases when we subtract the second line from the first one multiplied by a certain coefficient. Make sure that the free coefficient would be not be equal to zero:

{a+8k=07+bk=02−6k≠0⇒{k≠137−ab8=0⇒{k≠13ab=56⇒{a=nb=56nn∈R∖{−83,0}\begin{cases}a+8k=0\\7+bk=0\\2-6k\neq0\end{cases}\Rightarrow\begin{cases}k\neq\frac{1}{3}\\7-\frac{ab}{8}=0\end{cases}\Rightarrow\begin{cases}k\neq\frac{1}{3}\\ab=56\end{cases}\Rightarrow\begin{cases}a=n\\b=\frac{56}{n}\\n\in\mathbb{R}\setminus\{-\frac{8}{3}, 0\}\end{cases}⎩⎨⎧​a+8k=07+bk=02−6k=0​⇒{k=31​7−8ab​=0​⇒{k=31​ab=56​⇒⎩⎨⎧​a=nb=n56​n∈R∖{−38​,0}​

Otherwise, the system of equations would have a single solution.

Answer:

  • Infinite solutions:
    (ab)=(−83−21){a \choose b} = {-\frac{8}{3} \choose -21}(ba​)=(−21−38​​)
  • No solutions:
    (ab)=(n56n),n∈R∖{−83,0}{a \choose b} = {n \choose \frac{56}{n}},n\in\mathbb{R}\setminus\{-\frac{8}{3}, 0\}(ba​)=(n56​n​),n∈R∖{−38​,0}
  • Single solution: otherwise.
